##################
#Directory with example R code for the simulation results in 
#Fearnhead, Maidstone and Letchford "Detecting changes in slope with an $L_0$ penalty"
##################

The code uses the cpop package. The cpop package can be installed from the command line using:

R CMD INSTALL cpop_0.0.3.tar.gz

#################
CPOPexample_functions.R -- functions used in simulation study in Maidstone et al (2017).

These functions use the l1tf package, available from:
https://github.com/hadley/l1tf

#################

CPOPexamples.R -- example code for using CPOP code and for replicating results in Maidstone et al (2017). Calls CPOPexample_functions.R

#################

fig2_bfp_fast.txt -- Bacterial Flagellar data from Sowa et al. 2nd column is angular position (in terms of rotations).
